            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "If you don't want to have the verbose escaping of dot characters, you could also opt to use glob patterns and then match with `return vim.glob.to_lpeg(pattern):match(name) ~= nil`.\n\nBut isn't this what [`root_dir`](https://neovim.io/doc/user/lsp.html#vim.lsp.Config) is for? Or are you suggesting that glob patterns are so widely used that `root_markers` should also support them?",
